The paper deals with image-based sequence recognition, specifically in the context of scene text recognition. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed neural network architecture is end-to-end trainable, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on standard benchmarks, indicating a focus on evaluation and performance analysis (cs.IR).
